public class Queries

anatomyQuery

private java.lang.String anatomyQuery
INPUT: An anatomical entity (E) This query finds all the phenotypes (P) associated with a given anatomical entity. From the found phenotypes (P), this query finds the related taxa (T), genes (G), qualities (Q), and characters (C)that these qualities (Q) are attributes of

geneSummaryQuery

private java.lang.String geneSummaryQuery
INPUT: A gene (G) This query finds the anatomical entity - quality (EQ) combinations expressed by the input gene. Then it finds the characters (C) for the qualities (Q) directly associated with the gene to find a list of entity-character (EC) combinations. Lastly, it finds all the taxa (T) and genes (G) that are associated with phenotypes (P), that are associated with the (EC) combinations

taxonQuery

private java.lang.String taxonQuery
INPUT: A taxon (T) This query retrieves all the entities (E), qualities (Q), and characters (C) that are associated with the input taxon (T) and its subtaxa (ST)

geneQuery

private java.lang.String geneQuery
INPUT: A gene (G) This query retrieves all the Entities (E), Qualities (Q), and Characters (C) associated with the given gene (G) through the expressed phenotypes (P)

taxonSummaryQuery

private java.lang.String taxonSummaryQuery
INPUT: A taxon (T)\n This query finds all the phenotypes (P) directly associated with input taxon (T) and its subtaxa (ST). Then it retrieves the unique Entity-Character (EC) combinations from the phenotypes (P). Lastly, it finds all the genes (G) associated with the EC combinations that are also associated with the taxa and its subtaxa

homologyQuery

private java.lang.String homologyQuery
INPUT - An anatomical entity (E) This query finds all the homologous entities (E1) and associated taxa (T1) of a given input entity (E). The referenced publications and evidence codes are also retrieved.

freeTextDataQuery

private java.lang.String freeTextDataQuery
INPUT a reif_link_node_id that keeps track of metadata about the assertion\n This query is used to retrieve metadata about a assertion, such as publications, text notes about the state and character, and the curators names as well. The triple is retrieved as well
